    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-08-29T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-08-29T16:00:00-05:00" n="172"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d172">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.5018/6: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-08-29T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 29, 1942—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>227. Your 271, August 26. Department approves your recommendation and authorizes
                    you to join British in insisting that Iranians take all possible steps to effect
                    efficient control and distribution of domestic wheat supplies before requesting
                    further imports.</p>
                <p>In taking this action we have in mind imminent departure of Sheridan,<note n="43"
                        xml:id="d172fn43">J. P. Sheridan, appointed as Food and Supply Adviser to
                        the Iranian Government.</note> who should be of great assistance in
                    straightening out internal organization.</p>
                <p>Kidd,<note n="44" xml:id="d172fn44">Philip Kidd, Lend-Lease representative in
                        Iran.</note> who should be able to help with work of transport board, was to
                    leave London August 27 for Tehran via Cairo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
